# Bug repro: the "paused (filter)" chip is dead code in commit 54301a9.
#
# pause_chip = " · paused (filter)" is computed when p.paused = true
# and p.paused_by_user = false — but it is only spliced into the
# header_text ELSE branches (filter_mode = false paths). When
# filter_mode = true the title uses a different format string that
# omits pause_chip entirely. Since p.paused is set true by the same
# key press that sets filter_mode = true, and cleared back to false
# on Esc/Enter (same time filter_mode is cleared), the chip can never
# be rendered.
#
# What we CAN verify: the dashboard opens, filter mode works, and
# the title DOES change when / is pressed.

write placeholder.txt x
open placeholder.txt

command ai.dashboard

# Without filter mode, normal title.
expect screen contains "sort:"

# Enter filter mode — the title changes to the filter-mode format
# (which correctly LACKS pause_chip — the bug is that it *should*
# show "paused (filter)" here but doesn't).
key /
expect screen contains "enter applies"

# Esc exits filter mode.
key esc
expect screen lacks "enter applies"
